text: DeKalb County ( ) is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, the population was 764,382, making it Georgia's fourth-most largest county. Its county seat is Decatur. 10% of Atlanta is in DeKalb county. ==References== Category:1820s establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:1822 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
